        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 23 at 4:20PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 419 PM EDT/319 PM CDT/, Doppler radar was tracking a strong
thunderstorm near Walkerton, or 11 miles southeast of La Porte,
moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Nappanee, Bremen, Walkerton, North Liberty, Wakarusa, Kingsford
Heights, Lakeville, Locke, La Paz, Kingsbury, Teegarden, South
Center, Salem Heights, Fish Lake, Tracy, Stillwell, Woodland,
Southwest, Linkville, and Lake Of The Woods.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
